{
  "stem": "2522.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They're-- they are picrate of mercury, so they're very easily exploded.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We lay the thing, and Bat'ko takes off with his assistant and leaves me on the track to wait till the last moment to see if the Germans will come in with an advance, what's called a draisine.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sometimes, the Germans had a little car go ahead of the main train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Well, apparently this was not a military train, but it was a freight train, nevertheless.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it did have a machine gun nest, but in the middle because, you know, you get so many machine guns.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so after I see that there was no advance car going-- usually, what they have, they have a car going out with a search light shining on the tracks.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the tracks are sufficiently glistening that if anything lies on the tracks, you could see it, you know, yards and yards away.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And usually they have some soldier, some disposal soldier, looking at this thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was none of them, so I just mounted the cap on the as I was taught, fastening it with tape.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the train was pretty close by that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Really, I mean, you could almost smell it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was that close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I start running down the embankment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Panicking, unfortunately, I didn't find the path, so I was running over freshly plowed ground, which was lucky, by the way, because it was soft mud.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But I couldn't run very fast.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I just managed to go maybe 50 feet, maybe 40 feet, and just about over my shoulder when I-- the engine comes to where I expect it to blow.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I hit the ground, and off it goes, just, just, you know, flying steam and metal parts all over the place, enormous amount of shouting.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
